<p>Chesapeake Bay area neighborhoods, including Shore Drive and Bay Colony, benefit from cooling bay breezes but require HVAC systems designed to handle high humidity levels year-round. The Hilltop area's elevated location provides excellent solar exposure with minimal shading concerns, making it ideal for maximum solar energy production. Great Neck and Lynnhaven neighborhoods feature many mid-century homes that benefit significantly from HVAC upgrades, as older systems are often oversized and inefficient for the local climate. Red Mill and Landstown areas, with newer construction, often have good existing ductwork that can accommodate high-efficiency HVAC equipment upgrades.</p>

